Cell.Text: By the divines! It really is you, the Dragonborn! I've never seen anything like that before! You took that dragon's very soul!
Yes.

[S] One evening of second seed, over twenty years ago, I received a letter from a masked woman under the cover of darkness. | She was hiding it well, but I could tell she was badly injured. | I found it very strange that someone like her would approach me, a lowly farm boy, | with what seemed to be, a very important message. | So, here we are, after over 22 years of waiting, I can finally pass it on. Here you go Dragonborn, I believe this belongs to you. | ...
What happened? I was somewhere else just a moment ago.
What are you talking about? You just absorbed it's soul! There was a flash of light, and now I'm talking to you. | It was all pretty far from normal in my opinion. I don't know what to think.
[S] G|Very well then. Come and see me when you are ready Dragonborn.
What is that?
[S] S|Here.

[S] G|I have potion of invisibility - I acquired it recently as part of my collection. | Go and crouch by the basement window over there, and drink it as soon as I let them in. Let's hope it lasts long enough. | Oh, and remember, be as quiet as you can, and most importantly - don't move.
S|Did you hear what they said? The Thalmor clearly have plans for us. I think we should leave for Odelia immediately.

The woman said I was to tell no one of the message you now have in your possession, or our meeting for that matter, | for it would put Skyrim in great danger - it was for the eyes of the Dragonborn only, should they appear one day. | ...and with that, she was gone. I never saw her again. Shortly after, the Thalmor came, asking about her...So what did I do? I lied to them. | I did not want to take part in the many dangers that were unfolding before me. | Looking back upon the events of that night, it would seem the Thalmor were very much pressed with following the masked woman, | rather than questioning the townspeople at great length.

[S] Of course, my curiosity forced me to - just look around you, the first thing I did was learn the written word, I also took up collecting artefacts. | Before long, I made the journey to Odelia. Alas, I couldn't make it past the main entrance, as the place was crawling with bandits. | I still hold fear for the good people here at the lumber camp, I did not want to get any of them involved in such dangerous matters. | Shamefully, I gave up, I chose to move on with my life. | I concluded that I was caught in a trap set only by myself - I was blindly chasing a power that wasn't meant for me from the very beginning.

Node.Caption: _arcEivindLoreBranch02Topic02: I assume you read the letter and travelled to Odelia?

Cell.Text: [S] I desperately wanted to read that letter as soon as possible, so I learned the written word, I also took up collecting artifacts...
Let's travel together.
[S] Good idea. I'll navigate for you.
[S] G|Alright, let us travel together then! I'll navigate for you.
What should we do Dragonborn?
Negotiate.
[S] G|Hmm...Yes, good idea, maybe we can find out what they want. I know what to do!
Sneak Away.
[S] G|Oh, yes! The window over there by the stairs, we can climb out of that! Hurry!
Fight!
[S] G|Alright! Your resolve is admirable Dragonborn. Let us take them head on!
How can I help?
Let's split up.
[S] G|Alright, I'll meet you there.
Let's travel together.
[S] G|Alright, Lead the way.
Can you navigate for me?
[S] G|Sure. I'll keep you updated on where you need to go.
I don't need you to navigate anymore.
[S] G|Alright then.
Can you give me directions?
[S] G|Sure thing.
[S] G|Remember Dragonborn, if you get lost, you can always read the letter for directions.
Let's split up.
[S] Alright.
Let's fight the Thalmor head on!

S|You are most welcome to go to the Thalmor Embassy on your own Dragonborn, but I will take no part in it. | I have no intention of taking them on single-handedly, it would be suicide from my point of view. | Either way, I'm headed for Odelia. What do you want to do?
What did you hear the Thalmor say?

S|Something about returning to the embassy upon contact. They must have been looking for at least one of us. | Clearly they know something. I think we should head for Odelia as soon as possible. | Hopefully we can beat them there, better keep an eye out too, they're probably already following us.
[S] I'm staying here. I have no intention of fighting the Thalmor head-on. That's just crazy Dragonborn.
I received your letter.
[S] G|I have a dangerous matter to discuss with you. Let us go where we cannot be heard so easily. Follow me.
I'm ready to speak with you.
[S] G|Of course, Follow me.
